<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-27',
    prompt: 'Research and create a detailed financial aid emergency plan including mental health-related expense categories and funding sources for unexpected therapy or medication costs',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Mental health treatment costs can create additional stress during college, especially when unexpected needs arise for therapy, medications, or crisis interventions. Research your college\'s emergency financial aid programs, mental health-specific grants or scholarships, and community resources that help students afford mental health care. Creating a financial plan for potential mental health expenses removes financial barriers to seeking help and reduces anxiety about the cost of treatment when you need it most.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-28',
    prompt: 'Create a comprehensive semester-by-semester academic plan that accounts for your mental health patterns and builds in preventive wellness strategies',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Planning your academic trajectory with mental health considerations helps you make strategic decisions about course timing, workload management, and semester balance before you\'re in crisis mode. Map out your degree requirements across all semesters, noting which periods might be more challenging and building in lighter course loads during traditionally stressful times like finals or major life transitions. This proactive approach helps you graduate successfully while maintaining your mental wellness throughout your college journey.'
  }
];</parameter>
