<parameter name="new_string">    category: 'research',
    helpText: 'Campus counseling centers can become overwhelmed with demand, especially during high-stress periods like finals or major life transitions, making external provider options essential for continuity of care. Research therapists, psychiatrists, and counseling centers in your college area who accept your insurance and specialize in young adult or college student mental health. Having established backup providers ensures you can access professional support even when campus services have long wait times or limited availability.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-31',
    prompt: 'Create a detailed daily routine template that balances academic demands with consistent mental health maintenance activities like exercise, meditation, or journaling',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Establishing a sustainable daily routine that prioritizes mental health alongside academic responsibilities creates structure and prevents wellness activities from being sacrificed during stressful periods. Your routine should include consistent wake and sleep times, dedicated blocks for mental health practices, regular meals, and realistic study schedules that account for breaks and self-care. Having a written template helps you maintain stability during chaotic college periods and ensures that essential mental wellness activities remain non-negotiable parts of your day.'
  }
];</parameter>
